 "lrc": "[00:00.24]Uh, check it.\n[00:01.44]Too many snakes in the grass?\n[00:05.68]Nah.\n[00:07.04]Too many names in the file.\n[00:09.44]Let’s sort it out.\n[00:11.20]They want the facts, so we give ’em the facts\n[00:13.76]Who’s that Snake? Let me bring it right back\n[00:16.48]One was the student, one was the boss\n[00:18.96]One was the clone who refused that loss\n[00:21.44]One had the anger, one had the blades\n[00:24.00]One wore the mask in another man’s name\n[00:26.24]Round and round, but the tree don’t lie\n[00:28.56]Now everybody say, “Codec live!”\n[00:31.04]Diggity-deep in the jungle, the story gets humble\n[00:33.84]A soldier met a teacher, then the whole world crumbled\n[00:36.24]She was the root, the truth, the pain in the boot\n[00:38.64]The one who taught the moves, then got framed by the suit\n[00:41.60]He was the student with the sneaky little mission\n[00:43.84]Crawling through the grass with a Cold War condition\n[00:46.32]Naked was the name before the legend got tossed\n[00:48.56]Then the medal hit heavy, now they call him Big Boss\n[00:51.04]Not the same as the clone with the bandana tied\n[00:53.44]Not the same as the blond with the venom inside\n[00:56.00]Not the same as the president swinging both blades\n[00:58.48]This is daddy of the drama from the old-school days\n[01:00.88]They want the facts, so we give ’em the facts\n[01:03.28]Who’s that Snake? Let me bring it right back\n[01:06.08]One was the student, one was the boss\n[01:08.40]One was the clone who refused that loss\n[01:11.04]One had the anger, one had the blades\n[01:13.68]One wore the mask in another man’s name\n[01:16.16]Round and round, but the tree don’t lie\n[01:18.16]Now everybody say, “Codec live!”\n[01:20.48]Now listen to the clone zone, grown from the genome\n[01:22.96]Three sons from the legend, but none had a clean home\n[01:25.44]First one solid, quiet with the sneaky stride\n[01:27.92]Sent to stop the walking tank with the nukes inside\n[01:30.56]He ain’t the father, he ain’t the teacher\n[01:32.88]He’s the cigarette shadow with the solo feature\n[01:35.60]Snow base, gray fox, rex in the fight\n[01:38.16]He’s the one who walks away when the world turns white\n[01:40.64]Second one liquid, all rage, all flame\n[01:43.44]Mad at his brother and mad at his name\n[01:45.68]Thought his genes got cheated, thought fate picked sides\n[01:48.16]So he built up a war with revenge in his eyes\n[01:50.80]Third one solidus, suit with the swords\n[01:53.28]Former big leader cutting through cords\n[01:55.60]Wanted free will, but he scarred the next kid\n[01:58.24]Tried to beat the system with the same thing it did\n[02:00.40]Who taught the first one?\n[02:01.44]The mentor, the root\n[02:02.64]Who became Big Boss?\n[02:04.00]The student in the suit\n[02:04.88]Who broke the war gear?\n[02:06.24]The solid one did\n[02:07.44]Who screamed “brother”?\n[02:08.64]The angry clone kid\n[02:09.92]Who swung two blades?\n[02:11.28]The third son, wild\n[02:12.64]Who wore the horn?\n[02:13.68]The phantom profile\n[02:15.92]Wiggity-wait, there’s another little riddle\n[02:27.60]A man woke up broken with a horn in the middle\n[02:30.24]Missing hand, bad dreams, memory stitched tight\n[02:32.72]Everybody said “Boss,” but the mirror said “right?”\n[02:35.36]He was the phantom, the decoy, the double\n[02:37.68]Built from the blast and baptized in trouble\n[02:40.24]Diamond Dogs bark when the whole base burns\n[02:42.64]He wears the big name while the real one turns\n[02:45.12]So horn head? Phantom.\n[02:46.48]Bandana? Solid.\n[02:47.76]Blond rage? Liquid.\n[02:48.96]Two blades? Solidus.\n[02:50.56]Eyepatch legend? Big Boss.\n[02:52.08]Teacher? The Boss.\n[02:53.12]Cowboy with the gun? Don’t trust him, he’s lost.\n[02:55.60]They want the facts, so we give ’em the facts\n[02:58.00]Who’s that Snake? Let me bring it right back\n[03:00.80]One was the student, one was the boss\n[03:03.20]One was the clone who refused that loss\n[03:05.84]One had the anger, one had the blades\n[03:08.40]One wore the mask in another man’s name\n[03:10.96]Round and round, but the tree don’t lie\n[03:13.12]Now everybody say, “Codec live!”\n[03:15.12]Now the cowboy kept spinning with a grin and a plan\n[03:18.24]Playing every little side like a card in his hand\n[03:20.72]Son of the mentor, but he kept that low\n[03:23.36]Triple-cross rhythm in a wild west show\n[03:25.76]Then the hidden machine put the world in a cage\n[03:28.48]War became business on a digital stage\n[03:30.96]Truth got filtered, freedom got sold\n[03:33.36]Old Snake kept walking though his body got old\n[03:35.84]So the lesson ain’t just names in a folder\n[03:38.56]It’s sons, symbols, soldiers getting colder\n[03:40.96]One chose peace, one chased pride\n[03:43.68]One fought control, one lived a lie\n[03:48.32]They want the facts, so we give ’em the facts\n[03:50.88]Who’s that Snake? Let me bring it right back\n[03:53.76]Teacher, student, father, sons\n[03:56.24]Phantom, cowboy, Patriots, guns\n[03:58.72]Solid broke cycles, Liquid chased pain\n[04:01.12]Solidus cut wires in a president’s name\n[04:03.92]Round and round, but the tree don’t lie\n[04:05.92]Now everybody say, “Codec live!”\n[04:09.60]Teacher made student.\n[04:12.32]Student became legend.\n[04:13.76]Legend became father.\n[04:16.56]Father became clones.\n[04:18.64]One chose freedom.\n[04:20.40]One chose rage.\n[04:22.00]One chose rebellion.\n[04:22.96]One wore the mask.\n[04:23.27]Codec closed.\n[04:25.28]Now you know.\n"
